        <div class="spoiler-content">
          <div class="char-section">
            <h3 class="t-en">Notable Moments</h3>
            <h3 class="t-id">Momen Penting</h3>
            <p class="t-en">
              <em>The Scroll. Session II.</em> After the village entrance fight, while Nanang called
              about a basement and Traxex called about a gnome and the party attended to its competing
              priorities, Nero identified the actual problem. He went to town. He purchased a revival
              scroll. He returned and used it on Anaik. He did not announce this in advance. He simply
              resolved the situation in the order he had already decided was correct.
            </p>
            <p class="t-en" style="margin-top:0.8rem;">
              <em>The Lever. Session II.</em> Having positioned himself behind the windmill while the
              rest of the party fought, he turned off the mechanism. The gnome, attached to the arm,
              stopped. This was, considered narrowly, the favorable outcome. He then continued testing
              the lever. The windmill restarted. The windmill stopped. The gnome achieved velocity.
              His accounting, delivered through laughter: "I don't know, I don't know, I was just
              testing my thief skill on the lever." The chronicle has not found reason to disbelieve
              him, which is possibly the most unsettling conclusion.
            </p>
            <p class="t-en" style="margin-top:0.8rem;">
              <em>The Calculation. Session II.</em> Revived by Traxex's arrangement with the lich,
              he stood up. The first thing he did was identify that Traxex had taken six hundred gold
              from his chest despite having six hundred and forty-six of her own. He arrived at one
              hundred and thirty-six gold owed, wrote it down, and presented the paper to Traxex with
              sufficient persistence that the matter was eventually settled. The chronicle notes:
              he had just been dead.
            </p>
            <p class="t-en" style="margin-top:0.8rem;">
              <em>The Scroll (Burning Hands). Session II.</em> With the Warlord isolated on acid,
              Nero produced a scroll of burning hands: the correct tool, the right target, drawn
              with the efficiency of someone who has been cataloguing advantages since the opening
              exchange. He threw it at the Warlord. Nothing happened. Nanang, who was dying, laughed.
              The chronicle notes this not to diminish him. The same man who identified the scroll
              and its correct application simply could not make it work. Competence has limits.
              His are narrow and occasionally surprising.
            </p>
            <p class="t-en" style="margin-top:0.8rem;">
              <em>The Strongbox. Session II.</em> Last to leave the hill after the fight. Nanang
              had seen his hands near the strongbox the caravan members had been guarding. Nanang
              had not seen what followed. The chronicle also did not see what followed. This entry
              is recorded under the standing instruction on this page: note what he takes, what he
              says, and whether they match. The matching, here, remains open.
            </p>
            <p style="margin-top:0.8rem;">
              <em class="t-id">Gulungan. Sesi II.</em><span class="t-id"> Setelah pertempuran di pintu masuk desa, sementara Nanang berteriak soal ruang bawah tanah dan Traxex soal gnome dan rombongan sibuk dengan prioritas yang saling bersaing, Nero mengidentifikasi masalah yang sebenarnya. Ia pergi ke kota. Ia beli gulungan kebangkitan. Ia kembali dan gunakannya untuk Anaik. Ia tidak umumkan ini sebelumnya. Ia hanya selesaikan situasi dalam urutan yang sudah ia putuskan benar.</span>
            </p>
            <p class="t-id" style="margin-top:0.8rem;">
              <em>Tuas. Sesi II.</em> Setelah menempatkan diri di belakang kincir angin sementara rombongan bertarung, ia matikan mekanismenya. Gnome, yang terikat di lengan kincir, berhenti. Ini, dinilai secara sempit, adalah hasil yang menguntungkan. Lalu ia teruskan mencoba tuas itu. Kincir angin menyala lagi. Kincir angin berhenti. Gnome mencapai kecepatan. Penjelasannya, disampaikan sambil tertawa: "Tidak tahu, tidak tahu, aku cuma mencoba keahlian maling-ku di tuas." Kronik tidak menemukan alasan untuk tidak mempercayainya, yang mungkin adalah kesimpulan yang paling meresahkan.
            </p>
            <p class="t-id" style="margin-top:0.8rem;">
